The paper deals with the problem of spectrum sharing in cognitive radio systems, which is a topic related to information theory (cs.IT) and networked systems (cs.NI). The use of sensor nodes to collect information about the wireless environment suggests a focus on machine learning (cs.LG) and control systems (cs.SY). Finally, the development of a deep reinforcement learning-based method for power control indicates a strong emphasis on artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
